---

[00:06] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'In Gamestorm, you can wield a variety of tools in either hand. In your favored hand, press and hold the A or X button to summon the tool wheel. Then twist your wrist to highlight a tool. You will see that for each tool, there is an'

[00:19] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'information panel that provides the name of the tool and how to use it. Select the grabber tool and release the button to select it. As you do that, you will see what button you need to press in order to do what whilst using that tool.'

[00:32] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Do the same in your off hand and select the navigator tool. These are the recommended default selections for moving and interacting when designing in GameStorm. The grabber is the tool for'

[00:45] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'picking up things and placing them. It is the default tool on your favorite hand. Simply point the beam at something and pull the trigger to pick it up. As well as grabbing things at the end of'

[00:57] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'your pointer, you can also grab things by putting your hand into the thing\'s geometry. As soon as your hand intersects a face, it will turn from semi-transparent to solid, and you can then grab'

[01:09] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'it. Lightly press the joystick whilst holding something to see the radial menu options. Push left or right to rotate the object left or right. Push up to drop to the ground under gravity. Remember to keep hold of the trigger'

[01:23] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'until the thing has landed and stopped moving, or it can lead to unwanted movement when the timeline is played. This is very important when creating physics-based contraptions. And finally, pull down to bring something closer that'

[01:36] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'is far away. The navigator is the tool for teleporting around the set. It is the default tool on your off hand. Simply point where you want to jump to and a'

[01:48] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'green target circle will appear. The target circle won\'t appear if there is no collider or will turn red if it is not a valid layer to teleport onto. Using the radial menu, you can push left or right to turn 90° left or right. Pull'

[02:02] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'down to turn 180° to face the opposite direction. And finally, push up to reset your scale to one to one and drop to the ground directly beneath you. The'

[02:14] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'navigator also allows you to take control of characters. Point at a player character and hold down the trigger until you are the player to test some gameplay. Or point at a puppet character in order to enter the mocap setup room'

[02:28] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'before performing as them and recording some mocap animation. The duplicator lets you duplicate a single thing or a selected group of things. Simply point at the'

[02:40] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'thing you want to duplicate and it will highlight in green if it can be duplicated. Hold down the trigger to start a confirmation timer and keep holding until the thing is duplicated. Keep the trigger held down'

[02:53] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'until you have moved it to where you want it, then release. The destroyer lets you permanently remove things from the scene. You can delete a single thing or'

[03:05] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'a selected group of things. Simply point at something and it will highlight solid red if it can be deleted. Hold down the trigger to start a confirmation timer and keep holding until the thing is'

[03:17] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'deleted. The multiple select tool lets you create groups of things. Simply point at something you want to add to a group and click the trigger to add it and it will highlight in cyan. Click on'

[03:30] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'it again if you need to deselect it and lose the scan highlight. Or move the joystick in any direction to deselect all. Once you have created a group, you can move, duplicate, or destroy them as'

[03:44] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'a group. Grouping is very useful for quickly adding background scenery. Finally, if you press the B or Y button on your favorite hand whilst pointing at the group, you can inspect'

[03:57] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'what you have selected. This will reveal the inspector screen on your wristpad, allowing you to apply common properties such as locking them in the scene to avoid accidental movement or saving them to your asset library as a new grouped'

[04:09] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'asset for use in other games. The sketcher lets you create new shapes and work on existing shapes from the asset library. This is a powerful tool that we will'

[04:22] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'cover in another tutorial, but at its most basic, point at a surface and use the trigger to create a series of vertices with edges between them in a loop. These will be aligned to create a flat surface. And when you close the'

[04:35] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'loop, it will form a face and immediately extrude by 10 cm to create a 3D shape. This will be in edit shape mode with dark blue edges and visible measurements and angles in scan.'

[04:47] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'In this mode, you can then point at the faces, edges, and vertices of the shape. Then hold down the trigger to move them. With the sketcher still selected, you can also draw a line across a face to'

[05:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'subdivide it and add more detail. You can also do things like cut holes and extrude sections within faces, and by using combinations, do things like disable axis restrictions or scale'

[05:12] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'faces while extruding them. Should you accidentally drop out of edit shape mode, you can get back into it by pointing at the sketch, then holding down the B or Y inspect button'

[05:24] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'and rotating the inspect wheel menu to select edit shape. When the sketcher is selected, pressing the grip button will toggle between grid snap on and off. You can'

[05:36] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'change the grid size in the snap settings on the wrist pad. Sketches are by default white, but you can add color and texture to each face using the material screen on the'

[05:48] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'wristpad. The animator is one of the ways to create animation in GameStorm along with key frame, mocap, and physics. It allows you to pick something up with the trigger and move it with'

[06:01] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'your hand, recording its movement to the timeline. A confirmation timer will show before recording of the animation starts and it will move as if on a tight spring which helps to reduce hand jitter and results in a cleaner motion. Release the'

[06:14] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'trigger to stop recording and create a new activity on the timeline. You can play back or scrub time to see it animate along its new motion path. There are more functions available through the'

[06:26] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'timeline to edit the animation that we will cover in another tutorial.'
